10/11/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Officials say three men attacked Deputy Minister of Public Works and Reconstruction Lovre Pejkovic, who also heads the government's Office for Refugees, on the Karlovac-Zagreb motorway Saturday evening (8 November). The attackers reportedly came out of two cars that blocked Pejkovic's vehicle. They beat him until he became unconscious.
In other news, candidates of the ruling Social Democratic Party (SDP) were attacked with eggs and glasses during a weekend campaign rally in Imotski. SDP leader and Prime Minister Ivica Racan blamed the incident on the opposition Croatian Democratic Union, which denied involvement. (HINA, BBC - 09/11/03; MediaScan - 10/11/03)
